### ============================================================
### Auth — Refresh Token endpoints
### Base URL: https://localhost:49609
###
### Flow:
###   1. POST /api/auth/login          → { accessToken, refreshToken }  (via AuthController)
###   2. POST /api/auth/refresh       → { accessToken, refreshToken }  (rotate token pair)
###   3. POST /api/auth/revoke        → 204 No Content                 (invalidate refresh token)
###
### Notes:
###   - /api/auth/refresh is anonymous — no Bearer token required
###   - /api/auth/revoke requires a valid Bearer access token
###   - Reusing a rotated (spent) refresh token triggers theft detection and
###     revokes ALL tokens for that user
### ============================================================

@baseUrl = https://localhost:49609
@contentType = application/json
@token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN
@refreshToken = YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN

# ============================================================
# AUTH — obtain initial tokens
# ============================================================

### Login (get initial access + refresh token pair)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "admin@localhost",
  "password": "aDminN@W25!"
}

###

# ============================================================
# REFRESH — rotate token pair (anonymous)
# ============================================================

### Refresh token — returns new access token + new refresh token
# Expected: 200 OK  →  { "accessToken": "...", "refreshToken": "..." }
# Set @refreshToken above to the value returned by Login or a previous Refresh call
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###

### Refresh — invalid/expired token
# Expected: 400 Bad Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "refreshToken": "invalid-token-value"
}

###

# ============================================================
# REVOKE — invalidate a refresh token (requires auth)
# ============================================================

### Revoke refresh token
# Expected: 204 No Content
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/revoke
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###

### Revoke — attempt refresh after revocation
# Expected: 400 Bad Request  (token already revoked)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

###
